Well i haven't updated in awhile so i figured why not just let some peps out there know a alittle of what is going on in my life to date. Well to start off this semester isn't going to be as ruff as last semester well credit wise atleast. I mean i am still taking 16 hours which isn't bad but it is still alot more than what i used to take. The really cool thing about 3 of my classes though is that they are all design classes.  This means i get to pick either an empty lot around Las cruces or one that alreayd has a building on it and make it into our own design. I know to most of you guys you are thinking why the heck would that be fun but to me it is awesome. Another one of my classes i have about 8 peps in there that i know so in a classes of about 250 that is alot.  But there is another good thing this semester is that my roomie and i dont' have all our classes together. I mean it isn't bad when you live with someone, work with someone, and then go to all the same classes. NOT. It wasn't like we got on eachothers nerves all the time but atleast now we can have our own space. 
Now about this past weekend it was awesome one of the main reasons why i love being back in college. Well on friday dave and i made dinner for our new roomie leon, merrily, and katie(yes one of the many katies). Well after that leon had to go to band practice and we all stayed up till about 3:30 or 4 in the morning it was awesome. Then after we slept till about 1 Matt, Stev, and Andrew came over and the 6 of us went out shooting.  I guess all the years of Pappa teaching me how to shoot paided off cause i was nailing everything. After about 2 hours of that Sarah invited us over for lunch/dinner at her house. Gosh whenever she finds her husband he is going to be a lucky lucky man cause she can cook.  Well after a quick game of bball dave and i went to the night of poker at chris h. house. After about 7 hours of that dave and i were gone but the game continued for 2 more till 3 in the morning. As any sunday goes we went to church which Dennis has some amazing surmens. I think its so funny how so many pastors include their kids in their surmens. I always wonder if their kids know this and if they do how embaressed they are because of that. Well after lunch we meet up with a bunch of peps and played ultimate frizbe for about 2 hours. I never realized how much more i need to run until then. So now stev dave h and i are going to run all week long. Well that night the great girls made us breakfeast dinner which yet again was awesome. So after that dave matt and i had a guys night. Then on monday morning a group of about 18 of us went up to ruidoso for the day to go tubing. It was so fun. 6 hours of causing body harm to ourselves as well as eachother. Great pics if peps want to see. Well i am off hope to talk to you guys later. I am on on aol instant messenger any more so if you wanna chat drop me a line. Laterz

I found these pics on our Campus Crusade website its www.cccnmsu.com if you guys want to see more. These are of all us guys trying to relive the glory days of football. Thats me trying to throw the football Vince my bible study leader who is going to be getting married this may Phill being the awesome football player that he is (not being sarcastic) Oscar showing off his gun from highschool baseball Justin taking me out in a flag football game Chris Sheehan from the long line of great sheehan football players Me again (its my life journal gotta have a little more pics of me JK)
One of the many great cat naps taken at work. Dave trying to drink that whole thing at once and he actually succeeded!!!!

Well i think i am actually on a role 2 days in a row what are the odds of that happening.  After a long day at school i went to work which hadn't been fun just mainly fighting to do something but today that all changed.  It's crazy because today at the schools career fair i was handing in my resume and i am doing the job that they are doing now.  They looked at my resume and was all i am doing this too.  Then when i went to work i wasn't expecting much but that was an understatement.  Within 10 mins of walking in i was in a meeting with the 3 heads of my company till i left work.  Do you know when you have a project that you have made your baby. You lived breathed sweated and blead over it and then the bosses get ahold of it and their favorite thing to put on it was the big ol X thats what happened today.  But as they noticed that i was about ready to beat some ass cause they tore my baby apart one of my bosses turned to me and was all these X's are good.  Never have i ever thought that an X could be good but i guess they were. Due to the fact that in less than a month the computer program that I DESIGNED is going to be implemented in the company i work for.  
Well life has been pretty crazy lately due to the fact that 2 girls who in the past were my real close friends left and now  more are coming around.  So thanx to you ladies no need to say names because you know who you are and if you dont' shame on you.  
Thank God the week is almost over.  I more test then its clear sailing for me till this saturday when all hell is going to come loose.  For you guys who don't know the start of the big I-10 2 weeks has started.  This week we play UNM and next we play UTEP so its going to be pretty crazy.  The tailgates are going to be awesome as well as the game. We actually won our first game last week against TROY State.  So hopfully our guys can get on a role. 
Well off to study and go see the Harry Potter movie that i didnt' get to see when it was in the big theaters.

As i sit here i realize that its been a couple months since i have written in my journal it hasn't been cause i haven't wanted to but just that life has put many obstacles in my way.  First off if you all don't know i am taking 19 hours of class in engineering tech. So with those 19 hours of school a week i probably do about 2 to 3 hours per class of hw so that is 15 hours of hw. Now if you add the 19 hours of school and with the 15 hours of hw 34 hours right there. Secondly i am trying to work as many hours as i can but mostly i just work like 15 to 20. Now the grand total after work and school is between 49 and 54 hours a week of school and work. So i really don't have time for much of anything else. Schools pretty stressful sunday night till about thursday but after that its all home free.  I wanted to say to all those who i said i would send you letters and keep in contact with you better its been a ruff first month and a half of school but i will do my best to get things started but as you can see i don't have much time for any life outside of school and work. 
This semester has already been so crazy. First off one of my best friends from hs Emily is now engaged and is going to have a wedding next fall. How crazy is that? I never thought she would beat me to the big one there.  My ex is now with from what she has told me an awesome guy that really treats her well.  But one of the sad things is that these two women were my closest friends and now they dont' even talk to me for reasons that i have caused.  Its crazy how one decision may cause a reaction that will change your life forever. To those two if you ever read this sorry for my choices and best of luck with the men in your lives that should be in your lives. 
In the time that i do have this semester its been so awesome. I have 4 of my closest friends upstairs Chance, Josh, Sam, and Nan.  Then i live with an awesome guy Dave who at times we get on each others nerves but that is already accounted for since we have all the same classes and work together. The weekends are awesome here cause upstairs are Foreign peps. Yah you got it peps from france, germany, Australia and their friends are from many other countries.  I never thought until this year how hot an accent is for girls to have.  There is the a Swedish chick OMG and then there is a girl from france.  But if i have to say so the volleyball girls that have been hanging out upstairs because josh is dating a volleyball girl are the best looking girls around.  
Well i am off to do my hw so i will talk to you guys later.
